{"title_page": "Lake Creek High School", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n| name = Lake Creek High School\n| image = Lake Creek HS.jpg\n| established = 2018\n| motto = Stand with the Lions\n| other_name = LCHS\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| schooltype = [[High school#United States|high school]]\n| district = [[Montgomery Independent School District]]\n| grades = 9\u201312\n| principal = Phil Eaton\n| enrollment = 913<ref name=\"txschools\">https://txschools.gov/schools/170903004/profile</ref>\n| enrollment_as_of = 2018-2019\n| colors = {{Color box|#004076|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|#BEA564|border=darkgray}} Navy & Las Vegas gold\n| conference = [[University Interscholastic League|UIL]] Class 5A\n| mascot = Lion\n| campus = [[Rural]]\n| streetaddress = 20639 [[List of Farm to Market Roads in Texas (2800\u20132899)#FM 2854|FM 2854]]\n| city = [[Montgomery, Texas|Montgomery]]\n| state = [[Texas]]\n| zipcode = 77316\n| country = USA\n| homepage = {{URL|http://schools.misd.org/page/lchs.homepage}}\n| coordinates = {{coord|30.3489|-95.6656|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map = Texas#USA\n}}\n'''Lake Creek High School''' ('''LCHS''') is a high school in [[Montgomery County, Texas]], in the United States. It is the second high school built by [[Montgomery Independent School District]].<ref name=Olabi>{{cite web |last1=Olabi |first1=Nora |title=Montgomery ISD breaks ground on second high school |url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-ISD-breaks-ground-on-second-high-school-9502019.php |publisher=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=1 September 2016}}</ref>  The school was built after enrollment at [[Montgomery High School (Montgomery, Texas)|Montgomery High School]] exceeded building capacity. Lake Creek opened on August 21, 2018, for the 2018\u20132019 school year. The principal is Phil Eaton. The school is located on [[List of Farm to Market Roads in Texas (2800\u20132899)#FM 2854|Farm to Market Road 2854]]. \n\nLake Creek High School is named after the [[Lake Creek Settlement]]: an early settlement in [[Stephen F. Austin|Stephen F. Austin's]] Second Colony established before Texas' independence from Mexico.<ref name=name>{{cite web |title=New school names approved in Montgomery County |url=http://abc13.com/education/new-school-names-approved-in-montgomery-county/1345648/ |publisher=[[KTRK-TV]] |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=28 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n[[File:CDC Coronavirus Poster.jpg|thumb|200px|A CDC Covid19 poster at Lake Creek]]\nOn May 9, 2015, voters within Montgomery ISD's attendance zone voted in favor of a $256.75 million bond. The bond package included the construction of three schools: a high school, middle school and elementary school.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jordan |first1=Jay R. |title=Voters approve Montgomery ISD bond, trustee positions |url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Voters-approve-Montgomery-ISD-bond-trustee-9487931.php |publisher=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=9 May 2015}}</ref> The new high school was included to reduce enrollment at the district's other high school, [[Montgomery High School (Montgomery, Texas)|Montgomery High School]], whose student population had risen beyond the school's capacity.<ref name=Olabi/> Board members decided to name the new school after the [[Lake Creek Settlement]], the first Anglo-American settlement in Montgomery County.<ref name=name/> The district conducted a survey of future students to determine the school's mascot and colors.<ref name=Olabi/> The school opened in August 2018 at a cost of $98.28 million.<ref name=\"cimpact\">{{Cite web|url=https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/education/2018/08/20/gallery-get-a-sneak-peak-inside-montgomery-isds-lake-creek-high-school/|title=GALLERY: Get a sneak peak inside Montgomery ISD's Lake Creek High School|date=2018-08-20}}</ref> For the 2018-2019 academic year, the school opened with around 900 students in 9th, 10th, and 11th grades.<ref>[https://rptsvr1.tea.texas.gov/cgi/sas/broker?_service=marykay&_debug=0&single=N&batch=N&app=PUBLIC&ptype=H&_program=perfrept.perfmast.sas&level=campus&search=campnum&namenum=170903004&prgopt=2019/tapr/student.sas Texas Academic Performance Report: 2018-2019 Campus Student Information.] Texas Education Agency: December 2019. Retrieved December 22, 2019.</ref> The school fully incorporated seniors in the 2019-2020 academic year.<ref name=update>{{cite web |last1=Schafler |first1=Kelly |title=Updates on Lincoln Elementary School, Lake Creek High School: 4 takeaways from the Montgomery ISD board meeting Sept. 19 |url=https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/city-county/2017/09/20/updates-lincoln-elementary-school-lake-creek-high-school-4-takeaways-montgomery-isd-board-meeting-sept-19/ |publisher=Community Impact Newspaper |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=20 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe school was closed from March 11 to May 4, 2020 over fears of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/education/2020/03/11/montgomery-isd-to-close-early-for-spring-break-due-to-coronavirus-concerns/</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the 2018-2019 school year, LCHS had 913 students enrolled.<ref name=\"txschools\"/>\n\n*78.0% White\n*15.4% Hispanic\n*1.6% African American\n*1.8% Asian\n*1.0% American Indian\n*0.2% Pacific Islander\n*2.0% of two or more races\n\n22.2% of students were economically disadvantaged, 1.4% were English language learners, and 9.7% were students receiving special education services.\n\n==Academics==\nIn accordance with House bill 5 of the [[Eighty-third Texas Legislature|83rd Texas Legislature]], Lake Creek High School offers instruction in \"core foundation\" subjects and \"endorsement pathways.\" Foundation courses include traditional subjects such as English, math, science, and social studies. Originally, to fulfill the foreign language requirement, students could take either Spanish or French. After just one year, the school discontinued the French program, leaving only one language for students to take.<ref name=courses>{{cite web |title=Course Catalog 2018-2019 |url=http://schools.misd.org/page/CSG-Catalog1819 |publisher=Montgomery Independent School District |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref> \n\nHB5 designates four \"endorsement pathways\" that students may follow: Arts and Humanities, Business and Industry, Public Service and STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics). For Arts and Humanities, students at Lake Creek High School may take courses such as art, band, choir, dance, debate, journalism and theater arts. For Business and Industry, the school offers courses in agriculture, business, information technology and manufacturing. For Public Service, students may take courses in education, health science, fashion and law enforcement. For STEM, students make take courses in engineering or computer science.<ref name=courses/>\n\nFor the 2018-2019 school year, it was given an A rating by the Texas Education Agency.<ref>https://txschools.gov/schools/170903004/overview</ref>\n\n==Sports==\n\nThe school offers competitive athletics in the following sports: American football, volleyball, basketball, soccer, baseball, softball, track, cross country, swimming, tennis and golf.<ref name=courses/> Female students may also participate in cheerleading and the \"Royals\" dance team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lake Creek High School home page |url=http://schools.misd.org/page/lchs.homepage |publisher=Montgomery Independent School District |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Basketball===\nIn the 2019-2020 season, the boys' basketball team were regional semi-finalists. They were the first team from Montgomery County to advance to the fourth round since [[The Woodlands College Park High School]] did so in 2012.<ref> https://www.houstonchronicle.com/texas-sports-nation/highschool/article/Lake-Creek-gives-Montgomery-County-a-rare-15103530.php</ref>\n\n===Soccer===\n\nAfter an inaugural season with one win, Lake Creek's boys' soccer team was restructured.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/sports/article/BOYS-SOCCER-New-Lake-Creek-coach-seeks-defensive-14074011.php |title=BOYS SOCCER: New Lake Creek coach seeks defensive improvement, competitiveness |last=Maskulinski |first=Justin |date=2019-07-05 |work=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=2019-08-11}}</ref>\n\n==Campus==\nLake Creek High School has six athletic fields and a 996-seat auditorium.<ref name=\"cimpact\"/>\n\nIn March 2018 an area resident asked the district to construct a sound barrier so his house would get less noise from air conditioners used for the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ellsworth, Meagan|url=https://www.chron.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-resident-seeks-sound-barrier-to-muffle-12724043.php|title=Montgomery resident seeks sound barrier to muffle Lake Creek High School AC noise|publisher=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=2018-03-02|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\n==Attendance and feeder patterns==\nAt opening, all sophomores and juniors at Montgomery High School were allowed to choose which high school they attended through an \"intra-district transfer\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.misd.org/page/dis.lchs | title=Montgomery Independent School District}}</ref> This policy was walked back in 2019 by the school board. As Assistant Superintendent Duane McFadden explained, \"You don't get to choose what school you go to.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-ISD-to-vote-on-intradistrict-transfer-13718360.php|title=Montgomery ISD to vote on intradistrict transfer policy changes}}</ref>\n\nThe following elementary schools (K-5) feed into Lake Creek High School:<ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3781/0/Elementary%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf Elementary Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref><ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3778/0/High%20School%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf High School Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref>\n\n* Keenan\n* Lone Star\n* Stewart Creek (partial)\n\nOak Hills Junior High School (6-8) is the sole junior high feeder into Lake Creek High School.<ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3779/0/Junior%20High%20School%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf Junior High Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.misd.org/ Montgomery ISD]\n*[http://www.lakecreeksettlement.info/Lake%20Creek%20High%20School%20News%20Release.pdf Exciting Times as MISD\u2019s New Schools Named]\n\n\n{{Montgomery County, Texas Schools}}\n[[Category:High schools in Montgomery County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2018]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name = Lake Creek High School\n| image = Lake Creek HS.jpg\n| established = 2018\n| motto = Stand with the Lions\n| other_name = LCHS\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| schooltype = [[High school#United States|high school]]\n| district = [[Montgomery Independent School District]]\n| grades = 9\u201312\n| principal = Phil Eaton\n| enrollment = 913<ref name=\"txschools\">https://txschools.gov/schools/170903004/profile</ref>\n| enrollment_as_of = 2018-2019\n| colors = {{Color box|#004076|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|#BEA564|border=darkgray}} Navy & Las Vegas gold\n| conference = [[University Interscholastic League|UIL]] Class 5A\n| mascot = Lion\n| campus = [[Rural]]\n| streetaddress = 20639 [[List of Farm to Market Roads in Texas (2800\u20132899) the #FM 2854|FM 2854]]\n| city = [[Montgomery, Texas|Montgomery]]\n| state = [[Texas]]\n| zipcode = 77316\n| country = USA\n| homepage = {{URL|http://schools.misd.org/page/lchs.homepage}}\n| coordinates = {{coord|30.3489|-95.6656|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map = Texas#USA\n}}\n'''Lake Creek High School''' ('''LCHS''') is a high school in [[Montgomery County, Texas]], in the United States. It is the second high school built by [[Montgomery Independent School District]].<ref name=Olabi>{{cite web |last1=Olabi |first1=Nora |title=Montgomery ISD breaks ground on second high school |url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-ISD-breaks-ground-on-second-high-school-9502019.php |publisher=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=1 September 2016}}</ref>  The school was built after enrollment at [[Montgomery High School (Montgomery, Texas)|Montgomery High School]] exceeded building capacity. Lake Creek opened on August 21, 2018, for the 2018\u20132019 school year. The principal is Phil Eaton. The school is located on [[List of Farm to Market Roads in Texas (2800\u20132899)#FM 2854|Farm to Market Road 2854]]. \n\nLake Creek High School is named after the [[Lake Creek Settlement]]: an early settlement in [[Stephen F. Austin|Stephen F. Austin's]] Second Colony established before Texas' independence from Mexico.<ref name=name>{{cite web |title=New school names approved in Montgomery County |url=http://abc13.com/education/new-school-names-approved-in-montgomery-county/1345648/ |publisher=[[KTRK-TV]] |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=28 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n[[File:CDC Coronavirus Poster.jpg|thumb|200px|A CDC Covid19 poster at Lake Creek]]\nOn May 9, 2015, voters within Montgomery ISD's attendance zone voted in favor of a $256.75 million bond. The bond package included the construction of three schools: a high school, middle school and elementary school.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jordan |first1=Jay R. |title=Voters approve Montgomery ISD bond, trustee positions |url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Voters-approve-Montgomery-ISD-bond-trustee-9487931.php |publisher=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=9 May 2015}}</ref> The new high school was included to reduce enrollment at the district's other high school, [[Montgomery High School (Montgomery, Texas)|Montgomery High School]], whose student population had risen beyond the school's capacity.<ref name=Olabi/> Board members decided to name the new school after the [[Lake Creek Settlement]], the first Anglo-American settlement in Montgomery County.<ref name=name/> The district conducted a survey of future students to determine the school's mascot and colors.<ref name=Olabi/> The school opened in August 2018 at a cost of $98.28 million.<ref name=\"cimpact\">{{Cite web|url=https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/education/2018/08/20/gallery-get-a-sneak-peak-inside-montgomery-isds-lake-creek-high-school/|title=GALLERY: Get a sneak peak inside Montgomery ISD's Lake Creek High School|date=2018-08-20}}</ref> For the 2018-2019 academic year, the school opened with around 900 students in 9th, 10th, and 11th grades.<ref>[https://rptsvr1.tea.texas.gov/cgi/sas/broker?_service=marykay&_debug=0&single=N&batch=N&app=PUBLIC&ptype=H&_program=perfrept.perfmast.sas&level=campus&search=campnum&namenum=170903004&prgopt=2019/tapr/student.sas Texas Academic Performance Report: 2018-2019 Campus Student Information.] Texas Education Agency: December 2019. Retrieved December 22, 2019.</ref> The school fully incorporated seniors in the 2019-2020 academic year.<ref name=update>{{cite web |last1=Schafler |first1=Kelly |title=Updates on Lincoln Elementary School, Lake Creek High School: 4 takeaways from the Montgomery ISD board meeting Sept. 19 |url=https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/city-county/2017/09/20/updates-lincoln-elementary-school-lake-creek-high-school-4-takeaways-montgomery-isd-board-meeting-sept-19/ |publisher=Community Impact Newspaper |accessdate=12 June 2018 |date=20 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe school was closed from March 11 to May 4, 2020 over fears of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>https://communityimpact.com/houston/conroe-montgomery/education/2020/03/11/montgomery-isd-to-close-early-for-spring-break-due-to-coronavirus-concerns/</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the 2018-2019 school year, LCHS had 913 students enrolled.<ref name=\"txschools\"/>\n\n*78.0% White\n*15.4% Hispanic\n*1.6% African American\n*1.8% Asian\n*1.0% American Indian\n*0.2% Pacific Islander\n*2.0% of two or more races\n\n22.2% of students were economically disadvantaged, 1.4% were English language learners, and 9.7% were students receiving special education services.\n\n==Academics==\nIn accordance with House bill 5 of the [[Eighty-third Texas Legislature|83rd Texas Legislature]], Lake Creek High School offers instruction in \"core foundation\" subjects and \"endorsement pathways.\" Foundation courses include traditional subjects such as English, math, science, and social studies. Originally, to fulfill the foreign language requirement, students could take either Spanish or French. After just one year, the school discontinued the French program, leaving only one language for students to take.<ref name=courses>{{cite web |title=Course Catalog 2018-2019 |url=http://schools.misd.org/page/CSG-Catalog1819 |publisher=Montgomery Independent School District |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref> \n\nHB5 designates four \"endorsement pathways\" that students may follow: Arts and Humanities, Business and Industry, Public Service and STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics). For Arts and Humanities, students at Lake Creek High School may take courses such as art, band, choir, dance, debate, journalism and theater arts. For Business and Industry, the school offers courses in agriculture, business, information technology and manufacturing. For Public Service, students may take courses in education, health science, fashion and law enforcement. For STEM, students make take courses in engineering or computer science.<ref name=courses/>\n\nFor the 2018-2019 school year, it was given an A rating by the Texas Education Agency.<ref>https://txschools.gov/schools/170903004/overview</ref>\n\n==Sports==\n\nThe school offers competitive athletics in the following sports: American football, volleyball, basketball, soccer, baseball, softball, track, cross country, swimming, tennis and golf.<ref name=courses/> Female students may also participate in cheerleading and the \"Royals\" dance team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lake Creek High School home page |url=http://schools.misd.org/page/lchs.homepage |publisher=Montgomery Independent School District |accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Basketball===\nIn the 2019-2020 season, the boys' basketball team were regional semi-finalists. They were the first team from Montgomery County to advance to the fourth round since [[The Woodlands College Park High School]] did so in 2012.<ref> https://www.houstonchronicle.com/texas-sports-nation/highschool/article/Lake-Creek-gives-Montgomery-County-a-rare-15103530.php</ref>\n\n===Soccer===\n\nAfter an inaugural season with one win, Lake Creek's boys' soccer team was restructured.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/sports/article/BOYS-SOCCER-New-Lake-Creek-coach-seeks-defensive-14074011.php |title=BOYS SOCCER: New Lake Creek coach seeks defensive improvement, competitiveness |last=Maskulinski |first=Justin |date=2019-07-05 |work=The Courier of Montgomery County |accessdate=2019-08-11}}</ref>\n\n==Campus==\nLake Creek High School has six athletic fields and a 996-seat auditorium.<ref name=\"cimpact\"/>\n\nIn March 2018 an area resident asked the district to construct a sound barrier so his house would get less noise from air conditioners used for the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ellsworth, Meagan|url=https://www.chron.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-resident-seeks-sound-barrier-to-muffle-12724043.php|title=Montgomery resident seeks sound barrier to muffle Lake Creek High School AC noise|publisher=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=2018-03-02|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\n==Attendance and feeder patterns==\nAt opening, all sophomores and juniors at Montgomery High School were allowed to choose which high school they attended through an \"intra-district transfer\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.misd.org/page/dis.lchs | title=Montgomery Independent School District}}</ref> This policy was walked back in 2019 by the school board. As Assistant Superintendent Duane McFadden explained, \"You don't get to choose what school you go to.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/news/article/Montgomery-ISD-to-vote-on-intradistrict-transfer-13718360.php|title=Montgomery ISD to vote on intradistrict transfer policy changes}}</ref>\n\nThe following elementary schools (K-5) feed into Lake Creek High School:<ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3781/0/Elementary%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf Elementary Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref><ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3778/0/High%20School%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf High School Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref>\n\n* Keenan\n* Lone Star\n* Stewart Creek (partial)\n\nOak Hills Junior High School (6-8) is the sole junior high feeder into Lake Creek High School.<ref>[http://www.misd.org/page/open/3779/0/Junior%20High%20School%20Attendance%20Zones%202018-19.pdf Junior High Attendance Zones.] Montgomery Independent School District. Retrieved 29 December 2018.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.misd.org/ Montgomery ISD]\n*[http://www.lakecreeksettlement.info/Lake%20Creek%20High%20School%20News%20Release.pdf Exciting Times as MISD\u2019s New Schools Named]\n\n\n{{Montgomery County, Texas Schools}}\n[[Category:High schools in Montgomery County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2018]]\n", "name_user": "Stedil", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix wikilink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Creek_High_School"}
